---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Emperor of the Cherokee — Wonderfilled, Inc."
  description="A sweeping four-voice historical novel published on the 296th anniversary of Moytoy's coronation. The hidden history of a Cherokee empire — told in Testimony, Witness, Record, and Reflection."
>

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div style="
    min-height: 80vh;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    justify-content: flex-end;
    padding: 12rem 4rem 6rem;
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--ink2);
  ">
    <div style="
      position: absolute; inset: 0;
      background:
        radial-gradient(ellipse 60% 80% at 70% 40%, rgba(139,26,26,0.08) 0%, transparent 60%),
        radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 60% at 20% 70%, rgba(201,168,76,0.04) 0%, transparent 70%),
        linear-gradient(180deg, #111111 0%, #0d0a08 100%);
    "></div>
    <div style="position: relative; z-index: 2; max-width: 900px;">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">Historical Novel</div>
      <h1 style="
        font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
        font-size: clamp(3.5rem, 8vw, 8rem);
        font-weight: 300;
        line-height: 0.9;
        letter-spacing: -0.02em;
        color: var(--text-hero);
        margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
      ">Emperor of<br>the <em style="font-style:italic; color:var(--gold);">Cherokee</em></h1>
      <p style="
        font-family: 'Space Mono', monospace;
        font-size: 0.6rem;
        letter-spacing: 0.25em;
        text-transform: uppercase;
        color: var(--gold);
        margin-bottom: 1rem;
      ">Published April 3, 2026</p>
      <p style="
        font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
        font-size: clamp(1.1rem, 2vw, 1.4rem);
        font-weight: 300; font-style: italic;
        color: var(--mist2);
        max-width: 600px;
        line-height: 1.5;
      ">The hidden history of a Cherokee empire — told in Testimony, Witness, Record, and Reflection.</p>
      <div class="card-formats" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <span class="format-pill active">Novel</span>
        <span class="format-pill">Audiobook</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Synopsis -->
  <section class="inner-section" style="background: var(--ink);">
    <div class="two-col">
      <div>
        <div class="section-eyebrow">The Book</div>
        <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);">Four Voices. <em>One Empire.</em></h2>
        <!-- Book cover placeholder -->
        <div style="
          margin-top: 3rem;
          width: 100%;
          max-width: 320px;
          aspect-ratio: 2/3;
          background: var(--ink3);
          border: 1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.15);
          display: flex;
          align-items: center;
          justify-content: center;
          flex-direction: column;
          gap: 1rem;
          padding: 2rem;
          text-align: center;
        ">
          <p style="font-family:'Cormorant Garamond',serif; font-size:1.4rem; font-weight:600; color:var(--gold); line-height:1.2;">Emperor of the Cherokee</p>
          <div style="width:40px; height:1px; background:var(--gold-dim);"></div>
          <p style="font-size:0.55rem; letter-spacing:0.2em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--text-body);">Stephen Erin Dinehart IV</p>
          <p style="font-size:0.5rem; letter-spacing:0.15em; text-transform:uppercase; color:var(--gold-dim); margin-top:auto;">Wonderfilled, Inc. · 2026</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>On April 3, 2026 — the 296th anniversary of Moytoy's coronation as Emperor of the Cherokee — Wonderfilled published a novel that has been in development for years.</p>
        <p><em>Emperor of the Cherokee</em> reconstructs a chapter of American history that has been systematically overlooked: the moment when the Cherokee operated as a <strong>sovereign imperial power</strong>, with diplomatic standing, territorial authority, and a monarch recognized by European crowns.</p>
        <p>The novel is told through <strong>four interleaved voices</strong>:</p>
        <p style="font-size:1rem; color:var(--text-body); line-height:2;">
          <strong style="color:var(--text-hero);">Testimony</strong> — the witness accounts of those who were there<br>
          <strong style="color:var(--text-hero);">Witness</strong> — the perspective of outsiders watching history unfold<br>
          <strong style="color:var(--text-hero);">Record</strong> — the documentary evidence, the ledgers and letters<br>
          <strong style="color:var(--text-hero);">Reflection</strong> — the long view, looking back across centuries
        </p>
        <p>Drawing on years of historical research into the Cherokee Nation, British colonial records, and the broader context of 18th-century American geopolitics — this is a book about sovereignty, memory, and the stories we choose not to tell.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- About the History -->
  <section class="inner-section" style="background: var(--ink2);">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Historical Context</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem); margin-bottom: 3rem;">Moytoy of <em>Tellico.</em></h2>
    <div style="max-width: 800px;">
      <div class="about-text">
        <p>In 1730, Moytoy of Tellico was recognized as Emperor of the Cherokee by British colonial officials — a diplomatic acknowledgment of Cherokee sovereignty and political organization that most American history education omits entirely.</p>
        <p>The Cherokee had functioning governance, territorial authority, and the political sophistication to navigate the competing imperial pressures of Britain, France, and Spain simultaneously. <em>Emperor of the Cherokee</em> is the story of that navigation — and what it cost.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Press Quotes (placeholders) -->
  <section class="inner-section" style="background: var(--ink);">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Reception</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3.5rem); margin-bottom: 3rem;">What People <em>Are Saying.</em></h2>
    <div style="max-width: 800px; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0;">
      <div class="press-quote">
        <p class="press-quote-text">"A sweeping, rigorously researched reconstruction of a history most Americans have never been taught. Dinehart writes with the precision of a historian and the vision of a mythmaker."</p>
        <p class="press-quote-source">Advance Review</p>
      </div>
      <div class="press-quote">
        <p class="press-quote-text">"The four-voice structure is a formal achievement — each perspective illuminates what the others cannot see. A novel about the nature of historical record as much as the events it describes."</p>
        <p class="press-quote-source">Advance Review</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Buy / Audiobook -->
  <section style="background: var(--ink2); text-align: center; padding: 8rem 4rem;">
    <div class="section-eyebrow" style="justify-content: center;">Get the Book</div>
    <h2 class="section-title" style="font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 5vw, 4rem); margin-bottom: 2rem;">Available <em>Now.</em></h2>
    <p style="font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-size: 1.2rem; font-weight: 300; font-style: italic; color: var(--mist2); max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto 3rem; line-height: 1.6;">
      Hardcover, paperback, and ebook. Audiobook edition in development.
    </p>
    <div style="display:flex; gap:1.5rem; justify-content:center; flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a class="btn-primary" href="/contact">Inquire About Rights</a>
      <a class="btn-ghost" href="/projects">All Projects →</a>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top: 3rem; font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.15em; color: var(--text-body);">
      Available wherever books are sold · ISBN information on request
    </p>
  </section>

</Base>
